# test

Renders verification and testing criteria. The exact section header phrase `## [VERIFICATION & UNIT TEST CRITERIA` is a recognized signal for AI coding agents and must be preserved verbatim — do not paraphrase it.

# entity Input

- directive: 'test'
- name: the target being tested — optional (function name, entity name, or module name)
- body: test scenarios, edge cases, mock data requirements, and assertion criteria

# entity Output

```markdown
## [VERIFICATION & UNIT TEST CRITERIA{{#name}}: {{name}}{{/name}}]

Generate tests that explicitly cover every scenario listed below. Each edge case, mock data structure, and assertion described here must appear in the test output. Do not omit any scenario:

{{body}}
```

# rule

- name is optional. {{#name}}: {{name}}{{/name}} is a conditional block — included only when name is non-empty.
- When name is absent the header is: `## [VERIFICATION & UNIT TEST CRITERIA]`
- The section header must use the exact phrase `VERIFICATION & UNIT TEST CRITERIA`. Do not paraphrase — AI coding agents scan for this string.
- Multiple test blocks targeting different names render as separate sections.
- Multiple test blocks with the same name across cascade levels are merged in cascade order.
